'wc' displays by default the number of lines, words and bytes of a piped output stream.

useful parameters
-l  count lines
-w  count words
-c  count bytes
-m  count characters

EXAMPLES
# Count the number of files present in your home directory
ls ~/ | wc -l

# Count the number of characters (including spaces) in a text-file
cat file.txt | wc -m
